A class that implements the Graph interface using an adjacency list to represent the graph.

This class contains experiments related to Breadth First Search algorithm on different graph implementations.

Represents an edge in a graph.

Graph<V>
This interface represents a Graph data structure with vertices and weighted edges.

A utility class for generating random weighted graphs.
HashFunction<K>
The HashFunction interface defines the contract for an object that generates a hash code for a given key and a specified capacity.
Hashing
The Hashing class provides methods to generate vehicle data, and calculate collision rates for different hash functions.
HashMap<K,V>
The HashMap interface defines the basic operations that can be performed on a hash map data structure.
HashMapGraph<K extends Comparable<K>>
A graph implementation using HashMap to store the adjacency map.
LinkedListHashMap<K,V>
A hash map implementation that uses linked lists to handle collisions.
Modulus<K>
The Modulus class implements the HashFunction interface to provide a hash function that uses modulus calculation to determine the hash code of a key.
Multiplicative<K>
The Multiplicative class is an implementation of the HashFunction interface that uses the Multiplicative hash function to generate hash codes.
Node<V,E>
Represents a node in a graph.

A Pair class representing a key-value pair.
Route<K>
A class representing a route between two nodes in a graph, consisting of a distance and a path.

TreeHashMap is an implementation of the HashMap interface that uses a tree data structure to organize key-value pairs.

This class contains various utility methods for working with graphs.
VanetEntry
This class represents an entry in a Vehicular Ad-hoc Network (VANET).
